Package com.rb.biz.types

Class Symbol

java.lang.Object
com.rb.biz.types.Symbol
public class Symbol
extends java.lang.Object
This is a thin wrapper around a regular String, but it gives us type safety whenever we want to represent a ticker symbol for an instrument (stock or ETF).

The string has limitations on its length and content, but that covers every instance of security symbol we have encountered.

Stocks sometimes have ticker changes, where the symbol can change, even though the underlying traded entity is fundamentally the same. One such example was QQQ -> QQQQ -> QQQ. A Symbol / date combination is unique, and an InstrumentId always has a single Symbol on a given day; ticker changes cannot happen mid-day.

Note that, in general, symbols are mostly used for human-facing outputs, like log files that describe what happened, HTML pages that summarize trading activity, etc. It is very important that InstrumentId are used whenever possible.
